&lt;div id=&#34;TOC&#34;&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#responses&#34;&gt;Responses&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#evaluation-definitions&#34;&gt;Evaluation Definitions&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div id=&#34;responses&#34; class=&#34;section level2&#34;&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Responses&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Read through posts on &lt;code&gt;#pictures-of-evaluation&lt;/code&gt; and comment on at least one posting using the &lt;a href=&#34;https://slack.com/help/articles/115000769927-Use-threads-to-organize-discussions-&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;Reply in thread&lt;/a&gt; option foo &lt;img src=&#34;https://edp617.theoreticalphysed.com/img/lesson/slack_pop_menu.png&#34; /&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div id=&#34;evaluation-definitions&#34; class=&#34;section level2&#34;&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Evaluation Definitions&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Look through the &lt;a href=&#34;https://edp617.theoreticalphysed.com/handouts/Evaluation%20Definitions.pdf&#34;&gt;evaluation definitions&lt;/a&gt; document.
Think about which of those definitions fits best with your own view of evaluation, or if there are components of your view that are not addressed by any of those definitions. Then write a single post on &lt;code&gt;#evaluation-definitions&lt;/code&gt; describing your view of evaluation and how it connects with any or all (or none) of the definitions described.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
</description>
